Ana Gasteyer As Elphaba in Wicked

Ana Gasteyer, who created the role of Elphaba for Chicago's production of Wicked , is currently playing a 13-week limited engagement as the misunderstood green-faced witch in the hit musical at the Gershwin Theatre. She will stay with the Stephen Schwartz-Winnie Holzman musical through Jan. 7, 2007. Ana Gasteyer returning to Chicago

Ana Gasteyer âthe former "Saturday Night Live" cast member who originated the role of Elphaba in the Chicago production of "Wicked"âis coming back to Chicago this fall. Gasteyer will star (as Fosca) in Gary Griffin's upcoming production of Stephen Sondheim and James Lapine's "Passion" at the Chicago Shakespeare Theater . The cast also will include Kathy Voytkoâthe actress who understudied Stephanie J. Block in "The Pirate Queen" on Broadway and found herself frequently on stage playing Grace O'Malley. All in all, this is shaping up as a very high-profile show. Sets are by Eugene Lee and costumes by Paul Tazewell, who recently designed "The Color Purple" on Broadway. Given the small size of the theater, demand for tickets is likely to be high. "Passion" is slated to open in October in the Upstairs Theater at Chicago Shakespeare on Navy Pier. Tickets are already on sale. on in Chicago Shakespeare Theater Permalink
